      "creation_date" : 1590721713,
      "post_id" : 53198433,
      "comment_id" : 109793894,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "It&#39;s useful. <a href=\"https://github.com/google/guava\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">github.com/google/guava</a> Guava is a set of core Java libraries from Google that includes new collection types (such as multimap and multiset), immutable collections, a graph library, and utilities for concurrency, I/O, hashing, caching, primitives, strings, and more! It is widely used on most Java projects within Google, and widely used by many other companies as well."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 12105927,
      "reputation" : 209,
      "user_id" : 8844747,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-RsX9WzWUAgY/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAAc/fI_U4DxBUKs/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
