    "answer_id" : 53198433,
    "question_id" : 3110547,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You could actually go with:\n<code>Map.Entry&lt;String, String&gt; en= Maps.immutableEntry(key, value);</code></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1661378,
      "reputation" : 2216,
      "user_id" : 1529616,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 46,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/64304f7d04496fe26bae600e23617905?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "velocity",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1529616/velocity"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 19,
    "last_activity_date" : 1610488779,
    "last_edit_date" : 1610488779,
    "creation_date" : 1599388361,
    "answer_id" : 63763159,
    "question_id" : 3110547,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you look at the <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Map.Entry.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">documentation</a> of Map.Entry you will find that it is a static interface (an interface which is defined inside the Map interface an can be accessed through Map.Entry) and it has two implementations</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>All Known Implementing Classes:</em><br />\nAbstractMap.SimpleEntry, AbstractMap.SimpleImmutableEntry</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The class <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/AbstractMap.SimpleEntry.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">AbstractMap.SimpleEntry</a> provides 2 constructors:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><em>Constructors and Description</em><br />\n<strong>AbstractMap.SimpleEntry(K key, V value)</strong><br />\nCreates an entry representing a mapping from the specified key to the<br />\nspecified value.<br />\n<strong>AbstractMap.SimpleEntry(Map.Entry&lt;? extends K,? extends V&gt; entry)</strong><br />\nCreates an entry representing the same mapping as the specified entry.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>An example use case:</p>\n<pre><code>import java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.AbstractMap.SimpleEntry;\n\npublic class MyClass {\n    public static void main(String args[]) {\n      Map.Entry e = new SimpleEntry&lt;String, String&gt;(&quot;Hello&quot;,&quot;World&quot;);\n\n      System.out.println(e.getKey()+&quot; &quot;+e.getValue());\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
